The article applauds the UAW and General Motors for reaching a historic agreement after negotiations. The agreement provides workers with better pay, benefits, and respect. It also rewards autoworkers with record raises, more paid leave, retirement security, and more rights and respect at work. The UAW has now reached tentative agreements with all of the Big Three American automakers. The article also praises the decision to bring back all GM workers who were on strike. It emphasizes the power of unions and collective bargaining in creating middle-class jobs and helping American companies thrive. The final decision on the agreements will be made by UAW members in the coming days and weeks.